TY  - JOUR
T1  - A Model of Exchange Rate Dynamics
AU  - Mussa, Michael
Y1  - 1982/02/01
PY  - 1982
DA  - 1982/02/01
N1  - doi: 10.1086/261040
DO  - 10.1086/261040
T2  - Journal of Political Economy
JF  - Journal of Political Economy
SP  - 74
EP  - 104
VL  - 90
IS  - 1
PB  - The University of Chicago Press
N2  - This model treats the exchange rate as an "asset price" that depends on expectations concerning exogenous real and monetary factors that will affect relative prices and absolute price levels in future periods. Changes in exchange rates reflect both expected changes in these exogenous factors and changes in expectations occasioned by new information. The model explains the random component in exchange rate behavior, the source of divergences from purchasing power parity, the anticipatory response of exchange rates to future expected disturbances, and the causes of exchange rate overshooting.
AB  - This model treats the exchange rate as an "asset price" that depends on expectations concerning exogenous real and monetary factors that will affect relative prices and absolute price levels in future periods. Changes in exchange rates reflect both expected changes in these exogenous factors and changes in expectations occasioned by new information. The model explains the random component in exchange rate behavior, the source of divergences from purchasing power parity, the anticipatory response of exchange rates to future expected disturbances, and the causes of exchange rate overshooting.
SN  - 0022-3808
M3  - doi: 10.1086/261040
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1086/261040
Y2  - 2024/03/22
